body_html:
Hi @duplex143 ,

Where are you getting your .pb file? (It doesn't seem to be a TFLite compatible quantized graph) The instructions for creating a quantized TFLite graph are available here: https://www.tensorflow.org/performance/quantization

In particular your graph should include FakeQuant operations that store the quantization range information for TOCO.

If you are doing image classification, we have released pretrained (on Imagenet) models that are already in TFLite format: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/models.md

Hope that helps!

In particular your graph should include FakeQuant operations that store the quantization range information for TOCO.

If you are doing image classification, we have released pretrained (on Imagenet) models that are already in TFLite format: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/models.md
